3.title: Task Complete
3.content:
Thank you!

This task is done, and you can now close this tab and return to the surveys.

If you lost your place, you can go back to your email and use the link from there.

4.title: First
4.content:
In this experiment, you will be shown a series of items, and you will have to choose if they are NEW, OLD, or SIMILAR to those you have already seen.

We will look at some examples before you start.

But first, please enter a brief description of the device you are using so we can remind you to use the same one later on. For example, you might be using "the old laptop" or "Mom's iPad" or "my phone".

21.title: Get Ready
21.content:
To summarize: You will see a sequence of items. For each, choose if it is OLD, SIMILAR, or NEW.

When you enter your answer, the screen will show what button you pressed, but it will not indicate if you were right or wrong.

This task will take 15 to 20 minutes, with no breaks.

Click Continue when you are ready to start.

metadata.title: MST - Continuous Version for Phones
metadata.description:
Mnemonic Similarity Task - Continuous Version for Phones

This is like the other Stark-mirroring tasks in the repo, EXCEPT it is designed for button input on phones and has a 10 second maximum time per stimulus. [Also functions on tablets and computers.]
